{"key":"processedPost-8444209","value":{"id":8444209,"first":8444181,"last":8444233,"when":1211758010,"utime":"05/26/08 02:26 AM","content":"Never set cakes on perlite.  The mycelium will waste energy that <i>should</i> be used for fruiting, on colonizing a substance with no food.<br />4 to 5 inches of well drained perlite is recommended, not 1 1/2.<br />Mycelium on the stems is normal and not an indication of humidity.  After all, mushrooms <i>are</i> mycelium.<br />Dunking is to replenish moisture.  If you cakes are blue, they're dry.  Here ya go: <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/21149_7737.asp\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">http://www.mushroomvideos.com/21<wbr>149_7737.asp</a><br />RR","title":"Re: new and confused"}}